### <a id="_heading=h.z337ya"></a>Conclusion and Next Steps

To maintain and improve your site's performance, our primary focus will be on identifying and making the most of keyword opportunities\. Here is a detailed plan of action:

- Identify Keywords and Opportunities:
	- Conduct comprehensive keyword research to uncover broad, mid, and long\-tail keywords relevant to your industry\.
	- Map out these keywords to determine the best opportunities for content creation and optimisation\.
- Create New Meta Title Suggestions:
	- Develop new, optimised meta titles using the identified keywords\.
	- Ensure these titles are within the recommended character limits and are rich in relevant keywords\.
- Content Creation Strategy:
	- Use the keyword mapping and new meta titles to guide our content development\.
	- Focus on writing high\-quality, engaging content that targets identified keyword opportunities\.
	- Develop comprehensive articles, product descriptions, and service pages to enhance site relevance and authority\.

__OTHER AREAS OF FOCUS __

- Increase High\-Quality Inbound Links:
	- Implement strategies such as competitor research, directory submissions, and bookmarking sites to boost your link count\.
- Monitor and Reduce the Spam Score:
	- Maintain a low spam score through ongoing monitoring and proactive measures\.
- Address 404 Errors and Optimise Meta Titles:
	- Redirect existing 404 errors\.
	- Ensure meta titles are within the recommended character limits and contain keyword\-rich signals\.
	- Avoid repetition to prevent keyword cannibalisation\.
- Ensure Proper Site Indexation:
	- Perform regular checks using Google site search to verify that the site is indexed correctly\.
	- Optimise meta titles to include relevant keywords without excessive repetition\.
- Improve Mobile Optimisation:
	- Enhance site speed and user experience on mobile devices to positively impact overall rankings\.
